  "texts": [
    "Here we expand on their open-task grounded dialogue generation work and ground the language model on an arbitrary plan P j = (s j 1, s j 2,..., s j k).",
    "Also, to ensure a flexible tone-ofvoice, the assistant needs to attend to a tone-ofvoice instruction T j, i.e.",
    "neutral, somewhat polite, polite, or very polite.",
    "Hence, the initial input plan P j and the tone-of-voice T j, provide the LLM with the required grounding for the j th plan.",
    "Appendix A further details the tone-of-voice conditioned generation."
  ],
